usb: ohci-platform: add "spurious-oc" DT property (mirrors generic-EHCI)

The E1M-X carrier's USB over-current sense wiring is unusable (errata
E1M-X E3): the usb20-channel OVC input reads permanently asserted, and
since the GD32 supervisor SPI owns P9.6 the pin can no longer be parked
as a GPIO input to mask it.  ehci-platform already supports the generic
"spurious-oc" DT property for exactly this class of board; OHCI (the
usb20 companion controller) has no equivalent knob, so the false
over-current report cannot be silenced -- and OC events have functional
effect (hub port power-cycling), not just log noise.

Add the same property to ohci-platform: a new OHCI_QUIRK_SPURIOUS_OC
sets NOCP (no over-current protection) and clears OCPM in the root-hub
descriptor A during ohci_run, matching the EHCI behaviour and the
binding name.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [board-specific OC policy; the generic
binding addition would need to go through linux-usb]
Signed-off-by: Alp Lab AB

diff --git a/drivers/usb/host/ohci-hcd.c b/drivers/usb/host/ohci-hcd.c
index ab175e181e55..5da79a0daaf4 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/host/ohci-hcd.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/host/ohci-hcd.c
@@ -687,6 +687,14 @@ static int ohci_run (struct ohci_hcd *ohci)
 		 */
 		val |= RH_A_NPS;
 	}
+	if (ohci->flags & OHCI_QUIRK_SPURIOUS_OC) {
+		/* Board-level OC sense is miswired/unusable: disable
+		 * over-current processing entirely (NOCP), matching the
+		 * generic-EHCI spurious-oc behaviour.
+		 */
+		val |= RH_A_NOCP;
+		val &= ~RH_A_OCPM;
+	}
 	ohci_writel(ohci, val, &ohci->regs->roothub.a);
 
 	ohci_writel (ohci, RH_HS_LPSC, &ohci->regs->roothub.status);
diff --git a/drivers/usb/host/ohci-platform.c b/drivers/usb/host/ohci-platform.c
index fa27bbd68512..8714c57aef6a 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/host/ohci-platform.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/host/ohci-platform.c
@@ -136,6 +136,9 @@ static int ohci_platform_probe(struct platform_device *dev)
 		if (of_property_read_bool(dev->dev.of_node, "no-big-frame-no"))
 			ohci->flags |= OHCI_QUIRK_FRAME_NO;
 
+		if (of_property_read_bool(dev->dev.of_node, "spurious-oc"))
+			ohci->flags |= OHCI_QUIRK_SPURIOUS_OC;
+
 		if (of_property_read_bool(dev->dev.of_node,
 					  "remote-wakeup-connected"))
 			ohci->hc_control = OHCI_CTRL_RWC;
diff --git a/drivers/usb/host/ohci.h b/drivers/usb/host/ohci.h
index aac6285b37f8..026e9951139b 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/host/ohci.h
+++ b/drivers/usb/host/ohci.h
@@ -422,6 +422,7 @@ struct ohci_hcd {
 #define	OHCI_QUIRK_AMD_PREFETCH	0x400			/* pre-fetch for ISO transfer */
 #define	OHCI_QUIRK_GLOBAL_SUSPEND	0x800		/* must suspend ports */
 #define	OHCI_QUIRK_QEMU		0x1000			/* relax timing expectations */
+#define	OHCI_QUIRK_SPURIOUS_OC	0x2000			/* miswired OC sense; force NOCP */
 
 	// there are also chip quirks/bugs in init logic
 
